<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870514-0169 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor:Conventional Response</HL><DD> 05/14/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>   No, I haven't done an &quot;about-face&quot; (Letters, April 10). I've always been against calling a new Constitutional Convention for any reason because I don't think we can improve on the 1787 Convention that wrote our great Constitution.    It's true I helped to write the Republican Platform in 1984, but I opposed its sentence about a Constitutional Convention. I even opposed calling a new Constitutional Convention when the anti-abortion movement was demanding it in the 1970s.    Phyllis Schlafly   Alton, Ill.</TEXT></DOC>